h was the governor of his house. (Now Obadiah feared the LORD greatly:","year":-906},{"id":"recfOlNUt45ueomwR","ref":"1Kgs.18.4","text":"For it was so, when Jezebel cut off the prophets of the LORD, that Obadiah took an hundred prophets, and hid them by fifty in a cave, and fed them with bread and water.)","year":-906},{"id":"recGU1kr01SOfnbLJ","ref":"1Kgs.18.5","text":"And Ahab said unto Obadiah, Go into the land, unto all fountains of water, and unto all brooks: peradventure we may find grass to save the horses and mules alive, that we lose not all the beasts.","year":-906},{"id":"recsUZb1Mtwr6MoCZ","ref":"1Kgs.18.6","text":"So they divided the land between them to pass throughout it: Ahab went one way by himself, and Obadiah went another way by himself.","year":-906},{"id":"recsBdEnra5ThWMpa","ref":"1Kgs.18.7","text":"And as Obadiah was in the way, behold, Elijah met him: and he knew him, and fell on his face, and said, Art thou that my lord Elijah?","year":-906},{"id":"recO6Pl3iTz8eyOw9","ref":"1Kgs.18.8","text":"And he answered him, I am: go, tell thy lord, Behold, Elijah is here.","year":-906}]}
